t; have any validity.<br><br>In the high end game, it's not uncommon to have reached or surpassed the 1100AC mark.  At that point, other stats, hit points being a prime example, help a lot more than raising AC.  The high end encounters also change--when raiding, a paladin is often not the main tank, and if you don't get hit, well AC didn't help you much did it?  Many of these encounters have Area of Effect damage spells though, which again are not affected by AC.  Having higher hit points (and higher resistances) allows you to survive longer, higher WIS might give you enough mana to get off an additional heal, etc.<br><br>It also becomes increasingly common as you reach the high levels that you'll be with clerics who complete heal, at which point having higher hit points makes those complete heals more mana efficient.  Even if you're taking slightly more damage, your increased hit points might make up for it in those situations.  <br><br>If your hit points aren't at the level where complete heals make sense to use from a mana efficiency point of view, or if you solo or group with healing classes other than clerics, then AC (damage mitigation) would help more than hit points.<br><br>I think the bottom line is that AC is king up to a point--at that point it starts taking a back seat to other things.<br><br>Aalek<br>59 Knight<br>Reign in Power <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uthorena.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Thorena</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/22/02 5:46:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14987.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AC vs Stats revisited...not an equipment check :)</span><hr size=1> Based on what Ive been able to gather its AC vs Mobs Attack rateing.  Ie if you have 1200 ac and mob has 1000 attk you will get hit less and for less dmg.  When you go after uber mobs their attk rating is much higher.<br><br>Thor <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umystarria001.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mystarria001</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/22/02 5:54:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14987.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://server3005.freeyellow.com/mystarria101/allyour60.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AC vs Stats revisited...not an equipment check :)</span><hr size=1> I remember so long ago reading the AC vs Stat war. I was a half elf paladin wearing so much str/dex/wis gear I was getting my face bashed in. I overhauled to AC/HP and never looked back. I also made a HIE pally for the starting wis. +)<br><br>Exp grinding for me, the more AC/HP the happier you and your group will be. I can tank the lower end Gantru Moktor's with just me and my 55 chanter. <br><br>Raiding against AoE is all about resists.<br><br>Az <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ustratospaladin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>stratospaladin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/22/02 6:29:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14987.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AC vs Stats revisited...not an equipment check :)</span><hr size=1> I have personaly parsed loggs on this subject,  not quick to bleieve anything till I see it first hand (or atleast the trend).<br><br>@ 1000ac I would take 41dps (ground spiders in velks)/over 100 spiders parse<br><br>@ 1100ac I would take 32dps (over 400 spiders)<br><br>@ 1200ac I would take 24dps (over 500 spiders)<br><br>@ 1250ac I would take 21dps (300~ spiders)<br><br>@ 1300ac I would take 17dps (100~)<br><br>@ 1350ac I would take 15dps (100~)<br><br><br>that shows a trend of higher AC = less damage taken, but as you go up past 1250-1300 the damage taken/ac change ratio gets worse and worse.<br> <p><img src="http://www.boomspeed.com/jgable/newpic3.0.JPG"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uchartarus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Chartarus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/22/02 7:08:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14987.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://image.allmusic.com/00/amg/cov200/drd500/d535/d535012t38d.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AC vs Stats revisited...not an equipment check :)</span><hr size=1> depends on the mob too<br>if your getting hit by a flurry in ntov, then your going to see a lot better results with higher ac (more misses, better dmg mitigation)<br><br>personally if im tanking i go no less than 1500 ac (buffed), it makes a huge difference, luckily i dont give up many hps with a higher ac<br><br>there are a lot of variables in testing ac thou, but the best way is to test yourself, cause we will all fight different mobs, and are in different groups etc<br><br>i used to duo with an enchanter, so ac really didnt mean much (with slow on), so i could do a different gear setup with more resists<br><br>now that i solo mostly, i keep my ac high as possible, cause extra hps arent going to somehow reduce the dmg taken...only the percentage of dmg taken to my total hitpoints.  since when i solo i dont have someone casting CH on me, hit points are quite useless, and AC becomes the name of the game.<br><br>so really it all depends on what your doing <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=45274 " target="_blank">-Chartarus the lost paladud, Ayonae Ro</a> <br><ahref="http://pub69.ezboard.com/bvea " target="_blank"> Vea Victis</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utelumehtar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Telumehtar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 69<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/22/02 7:37:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14987.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AC vs Stats revisited...not an equipment check :)</span><hr size=1> From the observations I and some of my close friends who range from being warriors on to healers on to casters have come to this belief...<br><br>Level is God<br>AC is King (resists against AE mobs)<br>Stats are queen<br><br>In otherwords while AC is in fact the overall most important factor in armor it is not the ONLY thing.  there is a balance to be had and neglecting stats will see a decrease in perfermance.<br><br>As far as stats of importance to fighter types this is what has been gleaned.<br><br>STR is important to increase damage marginally and increase carry weight overall good to have some but not the stat that should be focused on too heavily.<br><br>STA is the king of melee stats.  Added HP and the reduction/elimination of being stunned from normal frontal attacks by many average mobs i.e. not bosses (the second point is debated but I have seen a large decrease in stuns<br><br>AGL if below 75 then 5 points are needed to &quot;fix&quot; the deficit.  The difference in AC made from 70 to 75 is often 40 to 60AC by the time you reach 50s.  Also further increases do increase AC but by such negligble amounts as to not be over concerning.<br><br>DEX is important to paladins since we get self procs and several of our holy swords make use of procs.  Also Dex helps in channelling spells.  A necro friend decked out in good dex gear is often quite able to still get barrages of spells off even with multiple dungeon creatures beating on him.<br><br>WIS is important cause we have some very nice spells which are VERY expensive to cast.  The healing wave spells are major mana hogs but are of such use on AE raids that they can literally turn a battle around.  Also we get many clerical buffs which due to hybrid penalty cost us 1.5 times the normal amount clerics pay.  And considering clerics complain about mana usage on buffs think of where that leaves us.<br><br>INT not so important to us but it does aid in the learning of skills.  If your working on a craft skill or even a weapon skill higher int has been linked to faster learning.<br><br>CHA Again not such a big deal for us except to make some extra money and get better deals off vendors.  However as Act of Valor is picked up as an AA skill I would like to see how CHA affects our chances of successfully coming back via the cleric Deathpact spell.  Awhile back there was heavy debate in the chanter and cleric forums that high charisma increased the odds that someone would bounce back after death from the Deathpact spell if they had higher CHA.  So this may end up being an important stat at the very end game.<br><br>Anyhow my point is while AC is indeed importantant if your faced with an armor choice where you could shave a few AC for some superb stats I would take the stats 9 times out of 10.  Couple that with the fact that most Velious and Luclin Armors come with stats anyhow it really become less of a sacrifice in the end.  Kunark armor was on the whole one of the silliest designs for armor I ever thought of, barring the BP legs and Helm (due to its effect). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubizomb.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bizomb</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 822<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/22/02 8:09:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14987.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AC vs Stats revisited...not an equipment check :)</span><hr size=1> Ac is king, but don't sacrifice all else for it. <br>Try to get as high ac armor as you can find. But don't feel like you can't dump a bit to balance out some stats or if you've got the choice between say 10str 5sta 6wis 10MR 5CR/FR or 8ac. It's pretty obvious to dump the ac for the stats. I would anyway. <br><br><br><br>Biz. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ustaticbb.showPublicProfile?language=EN>staticbb</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 86<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/22/02 9:46:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14987.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AC vs Stats revisited...not an equipment check :)</span><hr size=1> with about 1064 ac unbuffed id r