ole were going for stats. Then my focus shifted to getting more wisdom(level 50 fear era), then went on a hp craze(level 50 pre kunark). Then the shift was back to getting ac(mid 50s early kunark), then went on a hp craze(level 60 late kunark, velious era), now im back to shifting to mana/wisdom/mana regen again(late velious, luclin era). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utramausvoronadil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tramaus Voronadil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/22/02 11:32:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14987.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AC vs Stats revisited...not an equipment check :)</span><hr size=1> I have to say, I was getting a bit discouraged looking at all the high level profiles and then seeing my stuff. So I have to say your post did indeed give me a bit of hope, being I’ve been looking for that balance as of late (lack of money is depressing).<br><br>In any case since this isn’t an Equipment Check post/forum I won’t link my Magelo profile here (I’m still working on it anyway). But this AC discussion did bring up two questions:<br><br>There are two pieces of armor I’ve been thinking of replacing with better stats armor after I buy my FBSS (1.5K more to go (4K on my server)):<br><br>Deepwater Gauntlets – Gauntlets of the Black<br><br>Greaves of Ro – Crustacean Greaves<br><br>As a Half-Elf I NEED stamina, and the STR/WIS on the Gauntlets would be nice (and needed now that my Helm of Ro has been replaced with DW). So my question is this, I lose 1 AC on each of these items but gain stats that I definitely need. Should I go for this? I’m not going to ask for further suggestions because as I said, I’m just wonderi